Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2%medium} (see ingredients for amount), then quarter
lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into
1cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Add the cucumber and tomatoes to the dressing, toss to coat, then set aside.

Meanwhile, drain the @firm tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}.

When your chips are halfway through cooking, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in
a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently
to ensure it doesn't burn.

Stir the @korma curry paste{50%g} into the tofu and cook for ~{30%seconds}, then
add the @mango chutney{40%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for
amount).

Stir to glaze the tofu, then remove from the heat and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's a little dry.

When the tofu is nearly ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person)
onto a baking tray.

Pop onto the middle shelf of your oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, lay the warmed tortillas on your plates.

Spoon the glazed tofu along the center of the tortillas, then pile some of
the kachumber inspired salad on top.

Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}, then fold up the ends to
make your wraps.

Serve with the chips and remaining salad alongside. Enjoy!